RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Turf CR: 97. Starter Allowance Purse 40000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 7 Allowed 2 lbs. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANGELCENTS sprinted clear early and opened up a comfortable advantage, remained well in front along the rail through the turn, put to right-handed urging in the lane, weakened a bit late but was able to hold on. OVER ATTRACTED broke a step slow, unhurried in the early going, raced two wide into the turn then a bit off the rail, angled outside rival in upper stretch, flew late in the final sixteenth and just missed. READY JET GO broke a step slow, chased outside a rival then cleared that foe and moved to the inside around the turn, took aim while tipped out into the stretch but finished evenly in the final furlong. TAKE A LEAP came out a bit at the start, settled off the pace, rounded the bend two wide, drifted out from the left-handed in upper stretch, kept on through the final furlong but needed to find more. AUNT OPAL chased along the rail inside a rival into the turn, got put in tight past the three-eighths pole and lost ground, continued to save ground to the stretch and weakened. LITTLE RACHEL saved ground off the pace and failed to menace. SHEZA GIRLY GIRL bobbled a bit leaving the gate, trailed on the inside into the turn, exited the bend two wide and never threatened. HAND-TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 95. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 42000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD THAT HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OR THAT WERE RNA OR SOLD AT AUCTION FOR $150,000 OR LESS OR CLAIMING $62,500-$50,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, For Each $6,250 T o $50,000 1 lb. (For Eligibility Purposes, Refer To Most Recent Auction The Horse Was In).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLOONEY chased two wide through the first turn, remained off the rail in the middle stages then angled in for the far turn, gained while saving ground through that bend, rallied inside GOLDEN SOMBRERO next to the fence and drove past late. GOLDEN SOMBRERO took control from inside, set the pace with LOOKS RARE applying pressure, tried to shake free in the middle stages but could not, dueled past the quarter pole and maintained a short lead two wide into the stretch, bumped with LOOKS RARE in upper stretch, continued to battle with a slim lead in the final furlong, finally put away outer rival but could not fend off the rail rally from CLOONEY late. BLUE DOG bobbled slightly at the start, stalked in the three path early, went two wide into the far turn, spun four wide into the stretch, rallied five deep in the drive, drifted inward in the final furlong and gained the show. EXCEL CALCULATOR found a good spot inside stalking the pace, tipped three wide leaving the far turn, launched a bid four deep entering the furlong grounds, got floated in by BLUE DOG and got edged for the show. LOOKS RARE pressed the pace from outside, headed the leader with a quarter mile remaining, drifted in and bumped that foe in upper stretch, kept the pressure on to the sixteenth pole then faltered late. MUCINO chased along the three path early, trailed two wide on the second bend, steered out in the lane and failed to menace.

MAMBA COOL had to steady behind a rival early, stalked in the two path, raced between rivals on the far turn, three wide into the stretch and flattened. ORTH broke a step slow, stalked from inside then started to pull on the first turn and early on the backstretch, came two wide into the drive and weakened.
